subject: Disable auto activation of all volumes
revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2015-12-04 20:42:45.000000000', 'files': ['elements/puppet-stack-config/puppet-stack-config.pp'], 'message': 'Disable auto activation of all volumes

A problem was discovered that occurs during the provisioning of an
Atomic host with ironic causing a kernel panic. The problem is that
during provisioning the thin-pool associated with the provisioned VM was
being auto-activated on the instack host.

With containerized deployments becoming more popular, this is an
important fix to get in now. The workaround of defining the
auto_activation_volume_list to an empty list should be unobtrusive to
any operations on the undercloud.

Closes-bug: #1521733

Change-Id: I0ebb6488b0c061b0aed00ad1560126126ef3777c
'}]
commit_message:
Disable auto activation of all volumes

A problem was discovered that occurs during the provisioning of an
Atomic host with ironic causing a kernel panic. The problem is that
during provisioning the thin-pool associated with the provisioned VM was
being auto-activated on the instack host.

With containerized deployments becoming more popular, this is an
important fix to get in now. The workaround of defining the
auto_activation_volume_list to an empty list should be unobtrusive to
any operations on the undercloud.

Closes-bug: #1521733

Change-Id: I0ebb6488b0c061b0aed00ad1560126126ef3777c

commit_message:
make manual releases easier with option to generate announcement

Add -a option to release_from_yaml.sh and release.sh, causing the latter
to trigger announce.sh to generate the release announcement. This saves
a couple of extra manual steps, since the announce script can run
against the already cloned project repository with the new tag, instead
of having to do that step separately. The option is only meant to be
used when the scripts are run interactively.

Change-Id: I3449ca119d42c0317de2aa0fc5441091acfe49e1

subject: Fix method retrieving share capacity info
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-11-11 10:34:49.000000000', 'files': ['os_win/tests/utils/storage/test_smbutils.py', 'os_win/utils/storage/smbutils.py'], 'message': "Fix method retrieving share capacity info

This method uses the 'run_and_check_output' wrapper for executing a
kernel32 lib function. The issue is that the 'kernel32_lib_func' flag
was omitted, for which reason the error handling is done improperly.

Namely, this function will return non-zero values in case of success,
which at the moment is interpreted as an error.

This patch fixes the issue by adding the missing flag.

Change-Id: I63c7323ac9a5a4bd850971b2de67012b78bdbfa5
"}]
commit_message:
Fix method retrieving share capacity info

This method uses the 'run_and_check_output' wrapper for executing a
kernel32 lib function. The issue is that the 'kernel32_lib_func' flag
was omitted, for which reason the error handling is done improperly.

Namely, this function will return non-zero values in case of success,
which at the moment is interpreted as an error.

This patch fixes the issue by adding the missing flag.

Change-Id: I63c7323ac9a5a4bd850971b2de67012b78bdbfa5

commit_message:
Migrate "network list" command to new version using SDK.

This patch makes "network list" command use sdk.

Since we have to keep the other commands runnable with
the old network client, we use a temporary method to
create sdk network client. And as a result, the tests
need to patch a method to fake the temporary method,
which will be removed at last.

Change-Id: I0882501cd7bb2c17917e10a6da4298f1452c9765
Implements: blueprint neutron-client
Co-Authored-By: Terry Howe <terrylhowe@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Tang Chen <tangchen@cn.fujitsu.com>

commit_message:
Neutron FWaaS: Use generated configuration files if available

Generate the Neutron FWaaS sample config files by using the oslo
generator. The files are generated with a .sample extension and
replace the static example configuration files.

Once the generation code is delivered, the static config files
will be removed.

Change-Id: Ic8208850a27408c8fbeed80ecdb43345aa7dfaa4
Related-blueprint: autogen-neutron-conf-file
Partial-bug: #1199963

commit_message:
Avoid RequestContextSerializer from oslo.messaging

Oslo.messaging is in the process of removing the class
starting with the change id:
I21d76abf1c30b9e89cb8a6c20d1c0cc79cd83a3f

So ironic should just use its own class. Note that the
next oslo.messaging release will break ironic based on
some local testing.

Change-Id: I618fdc3024b3bc16515216bda900804f4cebba7d

When use 'sort-key=size' for multi-pages searching with postgreSQL
DB, it will raise an error: DBError: (psycopg2.DataError). And return
HTTPInternalServerError (HTTP 500) to users. The reason is that
postgreSQL doesn't support the size's default value to be string.
This patch set the size's default value to zero.

Change-Id: Ib3b5f3f57be3683ba274f0122e6314978a79e75f
Closes-bug:#1481154
"}]
commit_message:
Fix default value with postgreSQL

When use 'sort-key=size' for multi-pages searching with postgreSQL
DB, it will raise an error: DBError: (psycopg2.DataError). And return
HTTPInternalServerError (HTTP 500) to users. The reason is that
postgreSQL doesn't support the size's default value to be string.
This patch set the size's default value to zero.

Change-Id: Ib3b5f3f57be3683ba274f0122e6314978a79e75f
Closes-bug:#1481154

revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-12-08 16:29:20.000000000', 'files': ['nailgun/static/styles/main.less'], 'message': "Fix header layout after window's width has been resized down to <1285px

Bootstrap CSS sets negative margins to navbar rows, so in case we are
using more than one, successive rows are pushed to avoid overlapping.

Fuel web interface has only one navbar row, so the document layout
becomes broken when it pushes window margin beyond the viewport.

This commit cancels out negative margin-right if the navbar row is the

Safari 4+. Bug will be still observable in older browsers without
:last-child CSS3 selector support with no other regressions caused by
this change.

Closes-Bug: 1519375
"}]
commit_message:
Fix header layout after window's width has been resized down to <1285px

Bootstrap CSS sets negative margins to navbar rows, so in case we are
using more than one, successive rows are pushed to avoid overlapping.

Fuel web interface has only one navbar row, so the document layout
becomes broken when it pushes window margin beyond the viewport.

This commit cancels out negative margin-right if the navbar row is the
last child of its parent. It works in FF 3.5+, IE9+, Chrome 4+ and
Safari 4+. Bug will be still observable in older browsers without
:last-child CSS3 selector support with no other regressions caused by
this change.

Change-Id: I48a14b2321499e74a46d8f4cd61dc0f71a10fab4
Closes-Bug: 1519375

commit_message:
Use assertTrue/False instead of assertEqual(T/F)

The usage of assertEqual(True/False, ***) should be changed
to a meaningful format of assertTrue/False(***).
This patch fixes the same in keystone.

Change-Id: I2b67c34796c54b0963fbc7020d4e78ed4f71c7f3
Closes-Bug: #1512207

commit_message:
WIP: Set executor to Putils

The Brick library is dependent on Putils being the executor but
has the option to have a different executor passed in.  If a
different executor is used, it would cause issues in exception
handling.

This is WIP as the testcode needs a lot of clean-up due to
fake-exec being passed in as an executor.  I just wanted some
feedback on if this is the right path before fixing up all
the testcode.

Change-Id: I6fc0ee3ac67b1c2bd0db04cb3ec82fdb43a43184
Closes-Bug: #1216051

subject: Clean the unused methods in `volumes.py`
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-08-18 03:32:04.000000000', 'files': ['cinderclient/v1/volumes.py', 'cinderclient/v2/volumes.py'], 'message': 'Clean the unused methods in `volumes.py`

Methods in `volumes.py` are called by `shell.py` in two ways.

- Find the volume instance, call the method in class `Volume`,
  then execute the method defined in class `VolumeManager`.
- Call the method defined in class `VolumeManager` directly.
  For example, cs.volumes.set_metadata(volume, metadata) will
  invoke the method in `VolumeManager` instead of going to
  `Volume` at first.

In the second case, there is no need to define the method in class
`Volume`, this patch clean these unused methods.

Change-Id: Idbd63d0990944c1e3ea739ac842add1916df5989
'}]
commit_message:
Clean the unused methods in `volumes.py`

Methods in `volumes.py` are called by `shell.py` in two ways.

- Find the volume instance, call the method in class `Volume`,
  then execute the method defined in class `VolumeManager`.
- Call the method defined in class `VolumeManager` directly.
  For example, cs.volumes.set_metadata(volume, metadata) will
  invoke the method in `VolumeManager` instead of going to
  `Volume` at first.

In the second case, there is no need to define the method in class
`Volume`, this patch clean these unused methods.

Change-Id: Idbd63d0990944c1e3ea739ac842add1916df5989

commit_message:
Add support to return request_id of last request

Thread local storage is used for storing openstack request ids.

Added method 'store_openstack_request_id' which will store request_id
to thread local storage of client. This method is called after request
is made to cinder service.
If authentication fails or succeeds, in both the cases, request_id is
set to None because authenticate method will give a call to the keystone
service, and response header returned will contain request_id
of keystone service.

Added method 'get_openstack_request_id' which will return request_id
stored in thread local storage of client. 'get_openstack_request_id'
method should be called from cross-projects to retrieve the last
request-id from the client for logging purpose, after making api
call to cinder service.

Change-Id: Ie44df57f88584934e4d32da43ae58cc2d485aa74
blueprint: return-req-id

commit_message:
Add support to incremental backups in cinder

Added a new option to "cinder backup-create" to support incremental backups.
Specify --incremental to create an incremental backup. By default, it will
be a full backup.

Co-Authored-By: Xing Yang <xing.yang@emc.com>
Implements: blueprint incremental-backup
Change-Id: Id11ecd2982ea838181b4adaa5a742fc65f864acb

commit_message:
Remove fuel_package_updates module

This functionality is going to be covered by packetary
https://github.com/openstack/fuel-mirror/tree/master/packetary
which implements low level logic for manipulating of
rpm/deb packages and repositories. Packetary can be used
both for creating partial and full mirrors of upstream and MOS
repos.

Change-Id: I8f4ccc71a27a486e6b0042eed6ce2ca8098deb48
DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1517552

commit_message:
Allows for customization of NetworkDeployment actions

We don't necessarily want the network configuration to be reapplied
with every template update so we add a param to configure on which
action the NetworkDeployment resource should be executed.

Change-Id: I0e86318eb5521e540cc567ce9d77e1060086d48b
